The paper discusses distributed stream processing systems, which are typically used in data management and analytics. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of SQL, statistical inference, machine learning, and stream processing, which are all related to databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The experiments conducted in the paper also involve measuring latency and throughput, which are common performance metrics in machine learning (cs.LG) and networked systems (cs.NI).
